# [Goal Description]

Create a premium, 3-step signup process in [Signup.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/screens/Signup.vue) following the user's provided screenshots while maintaining the Frame 9 dark-mode aesthetic.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Logic & State Management

- **[NEW] [Signup.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/screens/Signup.vue)**
  - Implement a `currentStep` ref (1, 2, 3).
  - Step 1: Mobile input + Compliance.
  - Step 2: 4-digit OTP verification + Resend timer.
  - Step 3: Profile setup (Name, DOB).
  - Use `v-if`/`v-else` for step transitions.

### Navigation & Routing

- **[MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/router/index.ts)**
  - Register the `/signup` route.
- **[MODIFY] [Login.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/screens/Login.vue)**
  - Link the "Sign up as Player" button to the new `/signup` route.

 # Vue Router Restoration & Sync Plan

The current manual component switcher in [App.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/App.vue) bypasses the official Vue Router. This plan restores standard routing while maintaining the app shell, transitions, and shared state.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change will replace the manual `:is="currentScreenComponent"` logic in [App.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/App.vue) with `<router-view />`. Navigation will now be URL-driven, making the browser's Back/Forward buttons functional.

## Proposed Changes

### [Core Shell]

#### [MODIFY] [App.vue](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/App.vue)
- Replace manual component switcher with `<router-view />`.
- Use a `watch` on the route to keep `currentScreen` in sync for `BottomNav`.
- Move `selectedTournament` and `selectedCoupon` state management to a store/context provider.

### [State Management]

#### [MODIFY] [navigation.ts](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/frame9/src/stores/navigation.ts) [OR NEW contextStore]
- Add state for `selectedTournament` and `selectedCoupon` to handle cross-screen details without heavy prop drilling.

### [Screens]

#### [MODIFY] [Various Screens]
- Restore `router.push()` for navigation where appropriate.
- Fetch details by ID from store or use the shared state store.

